body:
I had a go, but I'm no coder so I just followed the example blindly:

```
		if len(gerr.Errors) > 0 {
			reason := gerr.Errors[0].Reason
			if reason == "rateLimitExceeded" || reason == "userRateLimitExceeded" {
				if f.opt.StopOnUploadLimit && gerr.Errors[0].Message == "User rate limit exceeded." {
					fs.Errorf(f, "Received upload limit error: %v", err)
					return false, fserrors.FatalError(err)
				}
				return true, err
			}
			if reason == "teamDriveFileLimitExceeded" {
				if f.opt.StopOnUploadLimit && gerr.Errors[0].Message == "Team Drive file limit exceeded." {
					fs.Errorf(f, "Received file limit error: %v", err)
					return false, fserrors.FatalError(err)
				}
				return true, err
			}
		}
```

That looks pretty good, I'd change this bit

```go
			if reason == "teamDriveFileLimitExceeded" {
				if f.opt.StopOnUploadLimit && gerr.Errors[0].Message == "Team Drive file limit exceeded." {
					fs.Errorf(f, "Received file limit error: %v", err)
					return false, fserrors.FatalError(err)
				}
				return true, err
			}
```

to

